{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 09:27:32.092273", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- localized faulty devices: server_access_router, load_balancer (10.200.0.7), backend_web_servers (10.200.0.3-10.200.0.6)\n- selected root cause(s): flow_rule_shadowing, load_balancer_overload, sender_application_delay\n\nNotes:\n- flow_rule_shadowing was chosen to reflect the missing/incorrect access-control enforcement allowing direct access to backend servers (policy rules not applied or shadowed).\n- load_balancer_overload and sender_application_delay were chosen to reflect the observed elevated HTTP TTFB and total response times pointing to load-balancer or backend application-side latency.\n\nIf you want, I can now run the targeted checks suggested in the report (server_access_router ACL/config, server host firewall rules, load-balancer and backend process/load metrics, iperf/bandwidth tests) and provide a prioritized remediation plan.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2816, "output_tokens": 200, "total_tokens": 3016, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
